rComments: Absolutely the best professor I have had.  A true inspiration.  Goldstein is passionate and cares about the students.  He always stays after class and is willing to chat and give exceptional advice.
He is a fantastic professor. Outlines course material and explains it thoroughly. Examinations are tough but few.

Fantastic class, great guy.  Awesome lectures - go to them, even though you don't have to.  But don't expect to be spoonfed the course material.  You have to figure it out for yourself and engage with it.  (Psst - that's a good thing.)
I learned much more from watching online videos about oral advocacy than I did in his class.

Goldstein is a phenomenal prof, one of the best I've had and perhaps the best at U of O law. If you can take Criminal Trial Advocacy with him, do so. You will make an oral argument every week. And his philosophy is to have you learn by doing. It works. He's also a good guy, generally speaking.
